  "original_title": "IMF \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dba\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dba \u0dbd\u0db6\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d9a\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dba\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Getting IMF support takes time",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe said that getting the support of the International Monetary Fund will take time and these crises will not be solved just by getting money from the International Monetary Fund or elsewhere. He said this while making a special statement in Kandy.",
        "\u201cMy objective was to reach an agreement (with the International Monetary Fund) in July. In the first week of August, the IMF Get approved by the board. Now it is delayed until the end of August.",
        "Because after the first week it's vacation time. Then we can approve it around September. No one else comes without this unity.",
        "IMF Don't think that this problem will be solved by going and taking money here and there. Our debt burden has increased. How do we pay this debt?",
        "We need more foreign exchange. New ways are needed. Our agriculture must be modernized. Do we look at this and work? Or say slogans?",
        "If we do not accept this challenge, this country will be lost. The next generation is cursing us. are we falling get up That is our challenge. Building a new Sri Lanka?",
        "Creating a new strong middle class? Are we creating an export-oriented economy? The current economy was created in 1977 by JR. Mr. Jayawardena. I am a part of it. The era of that economy is now over.\""
      ],
